New Records: Zach Edey made his debut for the Memphis Grizzlies against the Utah Jazz on October 23, 2024.
Key Match Events: The Memphis Grizzlies won the game against the Utah Jazz with a final score of 126-124.
Post-Match Reflections: Memphis Grizzlies coach Taylor Jenkins preferred Santi Aldama over Zach Edey for long stretches during the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zach Edey finished with five points and five rebounds after fouling out late in the fourth quarter.
